author: kfogel
msg: [Note to Greg H: totally a matter of personal taste how you do it in
code you're working on, but for code I "own" -- in the loose sense of
ownership, of course -- I'd like to stick to the pcalloc way.  In this
case, your change was not harmless, because d->prop_changed would now
have a garbage value, instead of the zero I was counting on from
pcalloc.  I know you don't favor this way of doing initialization, but
I personally find it less distracting, and would like to use it where
